Participant successfully connected apps.
Participant figured out that you can use glasses arm to control glasses. Informed her that we prefer only hand gestures for this study.
Participant accessed display and navigated to helpful gestures and tips.
Participant swipes thumb against index finger, but has trouble scrolling. Tries to close fist instead and has more success with scrolling.

Participant keeps hand up in almost same orientation as the selecting gestures when she is swiping, rather than closing her hand more like a first and swiping on the index finger like a touch pad.

Participant having trouble increasing volume either verbally or using gestures. Tried to use the phone buttons and that did help. Participant and moderator are now able to hear each other.
Participant notes volume is low again. Turned it up again with the phone buttons.
At 60 minute mark, participant moved to light green chair.
Participant notes that moderator begins to sound “far away again”. Notes that someone is behind her talking. Moves to the dark green chair,
Participant realizes that sound was coming through the iPhone, not the glasses. Used phone to select audio and change from iPhone to glasses. Now participant is able to head much more clearly.
Participant remains in dark green chair for scavenger hunt section.
